Frederick W. WILHELM et al. v. STANDARD OIL COMPANY (INDIANA) et al. No. 6095. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Nov. 20, 1936. Harrison E. Fryberger, of New York City, and Erwin Seago, of Chicago, 111., for appellants.

Before EVANS and SPARKS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for appellant, it is ordered by the court that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed without costs.
